2026-05-07 11:45:18,565 | AGENT | TechnicalArchitect Agent answered: To meet the client's expectations, I propose a cloud-native architecture that leverages our existing expertise in AI/ML systems, Cloud architecture, and API integration. Given the requirement for hosting on SecNumCloud-certified infrastructure within the EU, we can utilize Outscale (SecNumCloud) as our cloud provider.

For the AI/ML component, we can employ a containerized approach using Docker and Kubernetes (K8s) to deploy our LLM models, such as Mistral 7B or LLaMA 3, on GPU-accelerated instances. This will enable us to achieve fast response times and scale according to workload demands.

To ensure high availability, we can design a hybrid deployment with multiple Availability Zones (AZs) within the EU region, using Terraform for infrastructure-as-code management and Ansible for configuration management. Our containerization approach will also allow for seamless auto-scaling and rolling updates.

For API integration, we can utilize an API gateway like Kong or Apigee to manage incoming requests and route them to our LLM models. This will enable us to handle a high volume of concurrent requests while maintaining low latency.

To meet the response time requirement of < 2 seconds, we can fine-tune our LLM models using methods like LoRA or QLoRA, and leverage our experience with vector databases like Qdrant or Weaviate for efficient data storage and retrieval. Our inference servers, such as vLLM or Ollama, will be optimized for low-latency responses.

In terms of monitoring and logging, we can use Prometheus, Grafana, and the ELK stack to ensure that our system is performing within the expected parameters and to quickly identify any issues that may arise.

To achieve an availability of 99.9%, we can implement a comprehensive monitoring and alerting system, using tools like HashiCorp Vault for secrets management and CyberArk Conjug for secure access control. Our architecture will be designed with redundancy and failover capabilities in mind, ensuring that the system remains operational even in the event of component failures.

Overall, our proposed architecture will provide a scalable, secure, and highly available solution that meets the client's technical requirements while integrating seamlessly with their existing practices.
