Nexus Engineering S.r.l., in consortium with its specialized agents, proposes a comprehensive artificial intelligence solution to assist municipal agents of the City of Belval in their daily missions. Our proposal integrates AI/ML systems, cloud architecture, security compliance, legal adherence, budget optimization, innovation, and sustainability practices to meet the city's requirements for efficiency, quality of service, and regulatory compliance.

# Understanding of Requirements
The City of Belval seeks an artificial intelligence solution that assists municipal agents in accessing information, drafting administrative contents, instructing files, and facilitating collaboration. The solution must comply with GDPR, ensure data sovereignty, provide explainability and transparency, and be designed as a tool of assistance without automated decisions. It should integrate with existing systems, guarantee high availability (99.9%), and optimize costs within the global budget of 3 million euros over 4 years.

# Proposed Solution
Our proposed solution leverages a cloud-native architecture utilizing Outscale (SecNumCloud) for hosting within the EU, ensuring data sovereignty and GDPR compliance. We will employ Docker and Kubernetes (K8s) to deploy our LLM models, such as Mistral 7B or LLaMA 3, on GPU-accelerated instances for fast response times and scalability.

For AI/ML components, we propose leveraging our Large Language Model (LLM) stack, specifically the sovereign model Mistral 7B Instruct, which offers strong French-language performance and is self-hostable. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) capabilities will be used to provide contextualized answers by integrating with existing systems through dense vector semantic retrieval, BM25 sparse retrieval, and hybrid strategies.

To ensure domain adaptation and tone alignment, we will apply fine-tuning methods such as LoRA, QLoRA, or full fine-tune on the domain corpus. Explainability will be addressed through our XAI methods, including source citation, chain-of-thought display, SHAP for classification models, and LIME, with a low confidence threshold of 0.65 triggering an uncertainty warning and escalation to human supervisors.

Our security compliance measures include a standard data residency policy storing data within the EU only, anonymisation tools like Microsoft Presidio, access control standards such as multi-factor authentication and role-based access control design experience, and privileged access management solutions like CyberArk Conjur and HashiCorp Vault. Audit logs will be retained for 7 years, ensuring transparency and accountability.

Legally, we adhere to GDPR compliance through our Data Protection Agreement template version 3.2, support for Data Protection Impact Assessments, and a no-automated-decision-without-human-validation policy. Our experience with regulatory frameworks such as GDPR and the evolving EU AI Act regulations supports our ability to submit a compliant bid.

Budget-wise, we aim to optimize costs without sacrificing quality, considering our target gross margin percentage of 28%. We can absorb some reductions via rate renegotiation with subcontractors if the budget were to be reduced by up to 10%, but for larger reductions, scope adjustments would be necessary. Our standard daily rates and infrastructure margin will be used to estimate costs and potential margins.

In terms of sustainability, we propose leveraging our existing practices, including an EcoVadis rating of Silver with a score of 62, green hosting partners like OVHcloud and Scaleway who use 100% renewable energy, digital sobriety through methods like INT8/INT4 model quantisation, auto-scaling to zero outside business hours, query result caching, and a green IT hardware procurement policy. This approach contributes to reducing energetic consumption, aligning with the city's goals for sustainable development.

# Unaddressed Requirements
Given the information provided by our agents, all requirements specified in the call for tenders have been addressed, including functional scope, regulatory and legal constraints, technical constraints, sovereignty constraints, budgetary constraints, environmental constraints, and modalities of deployment. However, specific details on cost optimization strategies tailored to this project's exact needs and a detailed plan to exceed the city of Belval's sustainability goals beyond our standard practices are not provided due to limitations in the context data available to our Budget Agent and CSRSustainability Agent.

# Conclusion
Nexus Engineering S.r.l., with its consortium, is well-positioned to deliver an innovative AI solution that meets the City of Belval's needs for efficiency, quality of service, and regulatory compliance. Our proposal integrates cutting-edge technologies, ensures GDPR compliance, and optimizes costs while prioritizing sustainability. We are confident in our ability to deliver this project within the proposed timeline, adhering to all specified requirements and contributing positively to the city's digital transformation strategy.
