2026-05-07 12:03:52,067 | INFO | HTTP Request: POST http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/chat "HTTP/1.1 200 OK"
2026-05-07 12:03:52,067 | AGENT | SecurityCompliance Agent answered: To ensure compliance with GDPR and address the requirements for explicability of AI recommendations and human oversight over automated decisions, we will build on our existing security controls and measures.

Firstly, our GDPR posture already includes a Data Protection Officer (DPO) appointment, and we have experience in conducting Data Protection Impact Assessments (DPIA), which can be applied to the proposed solution. We also implement data subject rights such as access, rectification, erasure, portability, and objection.

For AI explicability, our AI security controls include output PII redaction, adversarial input detection, and confidence threshold escalation. These measures help ensure that AI recommendations are reliable and can be understood in the context of their limitations.

To prevent automated decisions without explicit agent validation, we will implement a human-in-the-loop review process for critical decision-making points. This involves designing our AI-powered information system to flag decisions that require validation by an authorized agent, ensuring that no sole reliance is placed on automated processing for decisions with significant effects.

Our access control standards, including multi-factor authentication (MFA) and role-based access control (RBAC), will be applied to ensure that only authorized personnel can validate decisions. The MFA methods we enforce include TOTP and hardware tokens (FIDO2), providing a robust layer of security against unauthorized access.

Furthermore, our audit and logging capabilities will be utilized to track all AI-driven recommendations and the subsequent validation or override actions taken by agents. This transparency is crucial for demonstrating compliance with GDPR principles of accountability and data protection by design and default.

Lastly, we will conduct regular DPIAs and privacy impact assessments specifically focused on the AI components of our solution to identify and mitigate any potential risks associated with automated decision-making and profiling under GDPR.
