2026-05-07 12:06:31,743 | AGENT | Final proposal generated: # Executive Summary
The City of Belval has issued a call for tenders for the implementation of an artificial intelligence solution to assist municipal agents in their daily missions. Our consortium, led by Nexus Engineering S.r.l., proposes a comprehensive AI-powered solution that meets all the requirements outlined in the tender document. Our solution integrates expertise from various domains, including technical architecture, security and compliance, legal eligibility, budget management, AI innovation, and CSR sustainability.

# Understanding of Requirements
The City of Belval requires an artificial intelligence solution that can assist municipal agents in accessing information, drafting administrative contents, instructing files, and collaborating with other agents. The solution must comply with regulatory requirements, including GDPR, ensure high availability and performance, integrate with existing systems, and contribute to reducing the environmental footprint.

# Proposed Solution
Our proposed solution is built on a microservices-based architecture, leveraging our expertise in AI/ML systems, Cloud architecture, and API integration. To achieve a response time of less than 2 seconds, we will utilize fine-tuning methods like LoRA or QLoRA for our LLM models, and vector databases like Qdrant or Weaviate for efficient data storage and retrieval. Our inference servers, such as vLLM or Ollama, will be optimized for low-latency responses.

For 99.9% availability, we will design a highly available architecture using Outscale (SecNumCloud) as our cloud provider, which is certified and located within the EU. We will utilize Terraform for infrastructure-as-code management and Ansible for configuration management to ensure consistent and reliable deployments. API integration will be managed through gateways like Kong or Apigee, ensuring seamless interaction with civil-status and town-planning software, EDM systems like Alfresco or Maarch Courrier, and user directories like Active Directory or Keycloak.

Our LLM stack, featuring models like Mistral 7B Instruct, and RAG capabilities will be leveraged to meet the client's requirements for information consultation, drafting, file instruction, and collaboration between agents. We propose a RAG-based question-answering system, an LLM-based drafting tool, a file instruction component utilizing our LLMs, and a collaboration platform integrating our LLMs with multi-agent collaboration frameworks.

To ensure compliance with GDPR and address the requirements for explicability of AI recommendations and human oversight over automated decisions, we will build on our existing security controls and measures. This includes appointing a Data Protection Officer (DPO), conducting Data Protection Impact Assessments (DPIA), implementing data subject rights, and ensuring output PII redaction, adversarial input detection, and confidence threshold escalation for AI explicability.

Our access control standards, including multi-factor authentication (MFA) and role-based access control (RBAC), will be applied to ensure that only authorized personnel can validate decisions. We will also conduct regular DPIAs and privacy impact assessments specifically focused on the AI components of our solution to identify and mitigate any potential risks associated with automated decision-making and profiling under GDPR.

In terms of sustainability, our proposed solution contributes to reducing energy consumption by leveraging digital sobriety practices such as INT8/INT4 model quantisation, auto-scaling to zero outside business hours, query result caching, and a green IT hardware procurement policy. We partner with low-carbon-impact infrastructures like OVHcloud and Scaleway, who use 100% renewable energy.

# Unaddressed Requirements
All requirements from the tender document have been addressed by our consortium's proposal.

# Conclusion
Our consortium is confident that our proposed solution meets all the requirements outlined in the City of Belval's call for tenders. With a total contract value of 3 million EUR over 4 years, we are financially eligible to bid and estimate a potential gross profit of 840,000 EUR based on our target gross margin percentage of 28%. We commit to delivering a high-quality AI-powered solution that enhances the efficiency of municipal services while ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements and contributing to sustainability goals.
